main event: A star-shaped object was observed in the skies of Dallas, Texas in September 1956.
interesting points: The object was initially stationary at 20,000 ft for 20 minutes before moving west at about 200 knots., The object changed color from white to red., The sighting lasted a total of 23 minutes., The investigation indicated the object might be an astro-body., The report confirms the object was real according to technical intelligence.
